title: ‘Superman’ Is About To Break A 17-Year-Old DC Curse
description: Superman's box office is about to reach a milestone that will break and almost 20-year curse over at DC, which is a miracle.
content:
Box office hounds are currently looking at the horse race between Superman and Fantastic Four, the former of which will apparently top the latter unless some dramatic shift takes place in the imminent future.

It’s not just a “win” for DC and the new DCU, it’s something that goes well beyond that. If this happens with Superman, and it’s almost certain it’s about to, this will be the first time a DC movie was the highest-grossing comic book movie of a given year since 2008. Can you guess what that was? Yep, Christopher Nolan’s The Dark Knight.

Of course, 2008 was also when the MCU began with Iron Man. The DCEU did not kick off until 2013 with Man of Steel, but in that five year gap there was nothing that topped Marvel (even The Dark Knight Rises), and even the biggest DCEU movie, Aquaman, did not beat out Marvel’s big entry that year, Avengers: Infinity War (of course it didn’t).

What’s the full list? I think it’s interesting to take a look at. I’m going to start at 2006 just to give a frame of reference (the previous two years were Marvel too, naturally):
• 2020 – No Marvel movies were even out due to COVID, DC had and Wonder Woman 1984, the latter of which was released simultaneously on HBO Max. Bizzare, bad year, as we all know.
• 2022 – Doctor Strange and the Multiverse of Madness
• 2025 – Superman, which will beat out Fantastic Four, Thunderbolts and Captain America: Brave New World this year.

Looking ahead to 2026 and beyond, this trend is unlikely to continue. If it hits its release date, the upcoming Spider-Man: Brand New Day is likely to crush Supergirl at the box office. After that, there are two Avengers movies that could go up against The Batman Part II one of those years, but I don’t think that would beat either.

Still, this is a significant achievement for Superman and DC. One that may not happen all that often from here, but with Marvel’s relative declines, who knows, it may start occurring more and more.

summary: The upcoming Superman movie, expected to break a 17-year-old DC curse, is set to become the first time a DC movie has been the highest-grossing comic book movie of a given year since 2008, according to The Dark Knight. This achievement is significant for both DC and the new DCU, as seen in comparison to Marvel's Marvel Cinematic Universe (MCU), which began with Iron Man in 2008 and the DCEU in 2013. Looking ahead to 2026 and beyond, this trend is unlikely to continue. However, with Marvel's relative declines, it may occur more often due to the decline of Marvel.
shortSummary: Superman is poised to break a 17-year-old DC Curse by becoming the highest-grossing comic book movie in 2016.

argos_summary: Superman is poised to become the highest-grossing comic book movie of the year, a title not held by a DC film since 2008's The Dark Knight. This potential success marks a significant moment for the DC Universe, especially as it competes against Marvel's offerings. Looking ahead, while Superman may lead in 2025, future releases like Spider-Man: Brand New Day and upcoming Avengers films could challenge DC's dominance.
